column5: Do you guys have any secrets for getting satellite views of a fly in lake? I know about all the standard ones like Google bing fish Canada But was wondering if there are any websites out there that offer a detailed satellite images that I may not know about
I like Zoom Earth. Similar to Google Earth, just different timing of images so might be better/worse than google earth depending on the location.
Just tried the zoom.Dont like it all rather just use the earth app.

I use all the above mentioned sites plus NASA EOSDIS Worldview.https://worldview.earthdata.nasa.gov/ I use that mostly to monitor ice out. I am assuming by "fish Canada" you meant Fish ON-line? I use the Ontario Map Viewer version. It is the same map as far as I know. Been really slow lately.https://www.lioapplications.lrc.gov....M&locale=en-CA
Thanks for the tips and correct about the fish on line Canada sight
